---
layout: post
title: "Product Teardown: Twitter"
date: 
---

User persona: completionist

Draw parallel to video games - people who spend countless hours completing every last side quest

You want to cater to those users. If they're set on reading every tweet, they'll see more ads!

Duplicate tweets and links. Should have an automated version of The Economist, Once.
	Removing duplicates also increases the ratio of ads to content
	It may alienate publishers

Losing your place when new tweets are loaded

App not loading any more tweets past a certain time. You just scroll down to a dot.
